# 🌾 Raithu Bazaar — Complete Website Roadmap

Everything you need to take this project from frontend-only to a fully production-ready platform with payments, delivery, and backend.

---

## ✅ Phase 1: Frontend (DONE)
All the following are already implemented:
- Landing page, Shop, Product Detail, Cart, Checkout
- Customer/Farmer/Captain/Admin dashboards
- Wishlist, Reviews, Notifications, Coupons, Recently Viewed
- Order tracking with timeline + review prompts
- Blog, Farmers Directory, Subscriptions, How It Works
- Multilingual support (EN/TE/HI)
- Responsive design + animations

---

## 🚀 Phase 2: Backend & Database

### Option A: Firebase (Recommended for solo dev / MVP)
| Service | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| **Firebase Auth** | Email/password + Google + Phone OTP login |
| **Cloud Firestore** | Store products, orders, users, reviews, wishlists |
| **Firebase Storage** | Product images, farmer photos |
| **Cloud Functions** | Order processing, notifications, admin triggers |
| **Firebase Hosting** | Free SSL, CDN, custom domain |

**Steps:**
1. Create Firebase project at [console.firebase.google.com](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Enable Authentication → Email/Password + Google
3. Create Firestore database with collections: `users`, `products`, `orders`, `reviews`, `wishlists`, `notifications`, `coupons`
4. Set up security rules (users can only read/write their own data)
5. Replace all `localStorage` calls in [app.js](file:///c:/Users/L/OneDrive/Desktop/farmer/app.js) with Firestore read/write
6. Use `onSnapshot()` for real-time updates (live order tracking, stock changes)

### Option B: Custom Backend (for scaling)
| Tech | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| **Node.js + Express** | REST API server |
| **MongoDB Atlas** | Free cloud database |
| **JWT** | Authentication tokens |
| **Multer + Cloudinary** | Image uploads |
| **Render / Railway** | Free hosting |

---

## 💳 Phase 3: Payments Integration

### Razorpay (Recommended for India)
- **Website:** [razorpay.com](https://razorpay.com)
- **Docs:** [razorpay.com/docs](https://razorpay.com/docs/payments/payment-gateway/web-integration/standard/)
- **Supports:** UPI, Cards, Net Banking, Wallets
- **Pricing:** 2% per transaction (no setup fee)

**Steps:**
1. Sign up on Razorpay → Get Test API keys (Key ID + Secret)
2. Install: `<script src="https://checkout.razorpay.com/v1/checkout.js"></script>`
3. Create order on backend → Get `order_id`
4. Open Razorpay checkout popup with order details
5. On success → verify payment signature on backend
6. Update order status to "paid"

### Alternative: Cashfree / PhonePe Business
- Similar setup, different pricing tiers

### Payment Flow:
```
Customer clicks "Place Order"
    → Backend creates Razorpay order (₹ amount)
    → Frontend opens Razorpay popup
    → Customer pays via UPI/Card/Wallet
    → Razorpay sends payment confirmation
    → Backend verifies signature
    → Order status → "Confirmed"
    → Customer gets SMS/email confirmation
```

---

## 🚚 Phase 4: Delivery Process

### How Farm-to-Door Delivery Works:

```
┌─────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌─────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐
│  ORDER      │ →  │  FARMER      │ →  │  CAPTAIN     │ →  │  CUSTOMER    │
│  PLACED     │    │  CONFIRMS &  │    │  PICKS UP &  │    │  RECEIVES    │
│             │    │  HARVESTS    │    │  DELIVERS    │    │  ORDER       │
└─────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └─────────────┘    └──────────────┘
```

### Delivery Models:

| Model | How It Works | Best For |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| **Hyperlocal (Same-city)** | Captains pick up from farmers, deliver same day or next day | Vegetables, fruits, dairy |
| **Hub & Spoke** | Products go to a central hub → sorted → dispatched | Grains, spices, bulk orders |
| **Direct Shipping** | Farmer ships via courier (Delhivery, Shiprocket) | Non-perishable items, pan-India |

### Delivery Tech Stack:
| Service | Purpose | Docs |
|---------|---------|------|
| **Shiprocket** | Courier aggregator (Delhivery, BlueDart, etc.) | [shiprocket.in/api](https://apidocs.shiprocket.in) |
| **Google Maps API** | Route optimization, ETA, tracking | [developers.google.com/maps](https://developers.google.com/maps) |
| **Twilio / MSG91** | SMS notifications to customer | [twilio.com](https://www.twilio.com) |
| **Firebase Cloud Messaging** | Push notifications | Built into Firebase |

### Order Status Flow:
```
Placed → Confirmed → Harvesting → Ready for Pickup → 
Out for Delivery → Delivered → Review Requested
```

### Delivery Implementation Steps:
1. **Zone mapping** — Define delivery areas by PIN code (already done in [app.js](file:///c:/Users/L/OneDrive/Desktop/farmer/app.js))
2. **Slot selection** — Let customers pick delivery date/time
3. **Captain assignment** — Auto-assign nearest available captain
4. **Real-time tracking** — Captain shares GPS location via Google Maps
5. **Proof of delivery** — Captain takes photo + customer OTP verification
6. **Returns handling** — 24-hour return window for quality issues

---

## 📱 Phase 5: SMS & Notifications

| Event | Channel | Service |
|-------|---------|---------|
| Order placed | SMS + Email + Push | MSG91 / Twilio + Nodemailer + FCM |
| Order confirmed | SMS + Push | MSG91 + FCM |
| Out for delivery | SMS + Push + WhatsApp | MSG91 + FCM + WhatsApp Business API |
| Delivered | Push + Email (receipt) | FCM + Nodemailer |
| Review reminder | Push (24h after delivery) | FCM + Cloud Functions scheduled |

---

## 🔒 Phase 6: Security & Auth

| Feature | Implementation |
|---------|---------------|
| **User auth** | Firebase Auth or JWT tokens |
| **Password hashing** | bcrypt (backend) or Firebase handles it |
| **Role-based access** | Admin, Farmer, Customer, Captain — check role on every API call |
| **Input validation** | Sanitize all form inputs (XSS prevention) |
| **HTTPS** | Required for payments — Firebase Hosting provides free SSL |
| **Rate limiting** | Prevent API abuse — use `express-rate-limit` |

---

## 📊 Phase 7: Admin & Analytics

| Feature | Tools |
|---------|-------|
| **Admin dashboard** | Already built — connect to real Firestore data |
| **Sales analytics** | Chart.js or Recharts — revenue, orders, top products |
| **Google Analytics** | Track page views, conversion funnels |
| **Hotjar** | Heatmaps, user behavior recording |
| **Error monitoring** | Sentry.io — catch JavaScript errors in production |

